<div class="container">

<h1>1. Shift Management</h1>

<p>
The Shift Management module enables police officers and emergency service personnel
to plan, create, and manage their work schedules efficiently.
</p>

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/shift-dashboard.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 1: Shift Management Dashboard</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>This feature allows users to:</h3>

<ul>
<li>Create individual shifts for specific dates</li>
<li>Generate repeating schedules using shift patterns</li>
<li>View schedules in list view and calendar view</li>
<li>Modify existing shift patterns and cycles</li>
</ul>

</div>

---

<h2>1.1 Shift Schedule Creation</h2>

<p>
Users can create schedules using the <strong>Create Shift</strong> option.
</p>

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/create-shift-menu.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 2: Create Shift Options Menu</p>

</div>

Users can choose:

<ul>
<li><strong>Custom Shift</strong> – Create individual shifts manually.</li>
<li><strong>Shift Pattern</strong> – Generate repeating schedules using cycles.</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>1.2 Creating a Custom Shift</h2>

<h3>Step 1: Access Custom Shift</h3>

<ul>
<li>Navigate to the Shift Management screen.</li>
<li>Tap <strong>Create Shift</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Custom Shift</strong>.</li>
</ul>

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/custom-shift-form.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 3: Custom Shift Creation Form</p>

</div>

---

<h3>Step 2: Enter Shift Details</h3>

<table>

<tr>
<th>Field</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Date</td>
<td>Select the shift date</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Shift Type</td>
<td>Day, Early, Night etc.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Working Hours</td>
<td>Enter start and end time</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Break Time</td>
<td>Optional rest period</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Colour Code</td>
<td>Colour used for calendar display</td>
</tr>

</table>

---

<h3>Step 3: Submit and Confirm</h3>

<ul>
<li>Tap <strong>Submit</strong></li>
<li>Review the confirmation screen</li>
<li>Tap <strong>Confirm</strong> to save the shift</li>
</ul>

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/shift-confirmation.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 4: Shift Confirmation Screen</p>

</div>

<div class="note">

The shift will appear in:
<ul>
<li>Shift Schedule List</li>
<li>Calendar View</li>
</ul>

</div>

---

<h2>1.3 Creating a Shift Pattern</h2>

<p>
Shift patterns allow users to automatically generate repeating schedules
using Shift Cycles.
</p>

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/shift-pattern-builder.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 5: Shift Pattern Builder</p>

</div>

---

<h3>Step 1: Create a Shift Cycle</h3>

<ul>
<li>Enter a cycle name</li>
<li>Add shift entries</li>
</ul>

<table>

<tr>
<th>Shift Type</th>
<th>Working Hours</th>
<th>Break</th>
<th>Duration</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Day Shift</td>
<td>09:00 – 17:00</td>
<td>1 hour</td>
<td>3 days</td>
</tr>

</table>

<div class="note">

<strong>Important:</strong>  
Every shift cycle must include at least one <strong>Rest Day</strong>.

</div>

---

<h3>Step 2: Add Cycle to Pattern</h3>

<ul>
<li>Specify number of repetitions</li>
<li>Add additional cycles if needed</li>
</ul>

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/pattern-cycle-add.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 6: Adding Cycles to Pattern</p>

</div>

---

<h3>Step 3: Generate Schedule</h3>

Users must provide:

<ul>
<li>Start Date</li>
<li>Number of Occurrences</li>
</ul>

The system then automatically generates the full shift schedule.

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/calendar-view.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 7: Calendar View of Generated Shifts</p>

</div>

---

<h2>1.4 Shift Pattern Creation</h2>

Users can create patterns in two ways:

<ul>
<li>Create a Custom Pattern</li>
<li>Use an Existing Pattern</li>
</ul>

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/pattern-selection.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 8: Pattern Selection Screen</p>

</div>

---

<h2>1.5 Shift Cycle Creation</h2>

A Shift Cycle represents a repeating sequence of shifts and rest days.

<div class="image-box">

<img src="images/cycle-creation.png">

<p class="caption">Figure 9: Shift Cycle Creation Screen</p>

</div>

</div>

